main event: A bright object was spotted high up in the sky in Sheboygan, Wisconsin on February 25, 1961.
interesting points: The object was silvery or golden in color.
It moved rapidly and disappeared over the horizon in about 30 seconds.
The object had no trail and made no sound.
The Air Force requested additional information but did not receive a photo or further details.
A later letter indicates the Air Force did not believe the sighting was related to Project Blue Book objects.
sighted object: a bright, silvery or golden object in the sky
